<title>HONG KONG: Interform loan increased to US$28 mln.</title>
<headline>Interform loan increased to US$28 mln.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Interform Ceramics Technologies Ltd said on Thursday its US$20 million loan had been increased to US$28 million after being oversubscribed.</p>
<p>Loan proceeds would mainly be used to finance its business distributing marble and ceramic tiles, and for working capital for the group, Interform said in a statement.</p>
<p>The loan was signed with nine financial institutions, including arrangers and lead managers Bali International Finance and The Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan, it said.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6371</p>
